.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-5::.
City: edinburgh, paris, berlin, liverpool
1. the person traveling to edinburgh is in an even position##4
2. the person traveling to berlin is on the right of the person traveling to edinburgh##1
3. the person traveling to paris is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3

.:: Answer ::.
|         |     1      |    2     |    3    |    4     |
| City   | liverpool | edinburgh | berlin | paris |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-6::.
4 different games are played: monopoly, poker, snooker, backgammon
1. the person playing poker is on the far right##1
2. the person playing poker is on the left or right of the person playing backgammon##3
3. the person playing snooker is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2     |  3   |    4    |
| Game   | snooker | monopoly | backgammon | poker |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 1x4-Level-4-7::.
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, motorbike, taxi, boat
1. the person driving the bike is on the left or right of the person driving the boat##3
2. the person driving the boat is in an odd position##4
3. the person driving the taxi is between the person driving the bike and the person driving the motorbike##2

.:: Answer ::.
|       |   1    |    2    |      3      |     4      |
| Transport   | boat | bike | taxi | motorbike |

